{"id":14881835,"mediaExerciseId":"4d4b1e6f-0b44-4f5e-8f8b-c8da2958bb25","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612488,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":788,"solutions":[{"id":6019464,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"To solve for the total amount of the option, we can use the formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Total Cost}&=\\text{Quantity} \\times \\text{Cost}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nSince we are dealing with bushels of corn, the contract size for this is always $5000$ bushels. Therefore, the total cost is:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Total Cost}&=5000 \\times \\$0.125\\\\\n&=\\$625\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe total cost for the option is $\\$625$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":364,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/fd5e4366063e5303519f03f229b51509/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":182,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/fd5e4366063e5303519f03f229b51509/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"If the price at expiration is $\\$3.74$ per bushel of corn, then the option will not be exercised since it is less than the strike price. Therefore, the net loss for this is the cost of the option which is $\\$625$.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/3f47cea7416275e229d757461d2d8edc/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/3f47cea7416275e229d757461d2d8edc/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"If the price at expiration is $\\$4.13$ per bushel, then the payoff can be calculated using this formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Payoff}&=(\\text{current market price} -\\text{strike price}) \\times \\text{quantity}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nSubstituting the values, we will get a payoff value of:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Payoff}&=(\\$4.13-\\$3.85)\\times5000\\\\\n&=\\$0.28 \\times 5000\\\\\n&=\\$1400\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":353,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/006f32e510d178473c6bd2359faec5d0/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":177,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/006f32e510d178473c6bd2359faec5d0/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"To get the total loss/profit, subtract the cost of the option from the payoff value\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{total profit/loss}&=\\$1400-\\$625\\\\\n&=\\$775\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nIf the market price at expiration is $\\$4.13$ per bushel, then the company will have a profit of $\\$775$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":273,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/6eea9608317e4e6e39b13d0eab587a36/lateximg_large.png","width":999},"regular":{"height":137,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/d2445bba571aec54de8daf58fc912cc2/6eea9608317e4e6e39b13d0eab587a36/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"4337579b-7ae1-4269-ac03-0b6d54916c42","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881836,"exerciseName":"4","page":788,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d3ffa1d2-feac-4c3a-bbc6-2c2272046abc","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-questions-and-problems-4-d3ffa1d2-feac-4c3a-bbc6-2c2272046abc"},{"id":14881837,"exerciseName":"5","page":788,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c5c5576a-0169-4a38-934a-41e4b39a12fd","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-questions-and-problems-5-c5c5576a-0169-4a38-934a-41e4b39a12fd"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881834,"exerciseName":"2","page":788,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8e888daa-098a-484a-8d53-e0b86d7dabe4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-questions-and-problems-2-8e888daa-098a-484a-8d53-e0b86d7dabe4"},{"id":14881833,"exerciseName":"1","page":788,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3cf8dd57-c694-4261-bfe4-10443b51b49f","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-questions-and-problems-1-3cf8dd57-c694-4261-bfe4-10443b51b49f"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-23-questions-and-problems-3-4d4b1e6f-0b44-4f5e-8f8b-c